# Normalize line endings to LF for all text files, regardless of the checking-out platform's
# core.autocrlf setting. Without this, a Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true silently
# checks every text file out as CRLF while the git blob stays LF — invisible locally, but it
# makes Prettier's `format:check` (LF by default) fail identically on every file, including in
# CI on a Linux runner that clones the repo directly (no autocrlf conversion involved there).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary/generated assets some tools might otherwise try to normalize.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
